<subSubSection id="0B736476B23B0F1BAC2025AEF3C6A15B" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B97F8242DDCD39D20009E5A67623555D" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3644E9BF6FFABEE7DFB84471F0A14DE" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Currently, two described species are assigned to this genus, however, there are five species represented in the NMNH collection. There is a need for a taxonomic revision of the group. 
<taxonomicName id="A24D69D7423BD6420EF83F49E9137086" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Anchomenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="CCBFE4EE24CA43ACDB8BCF130B172AF9" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Anchomenus elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831:725, was placed in &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="8EC71A637E73B93DD2AACE5D981EDAE5" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amphithasus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="903919DF18F2CF8B5995817508DA66A5" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Amphithasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; by 
<bibRefCitation id="A993C1E400D9E922480C9531BF96B000" author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" refId="B57" refString="Lorenz, W, 1998a. Systematic list of extant ground beetles of the world (Insecta, Coleoptera &quot;Geadephaga&quot;: Trachypachidae and Carabidae incl. Paussinae, Cicinidelinae, Rhysodinae). Privately published, W. Lorenz, Tutzing, iv + 502pp." title="Systematic list of extant ground beetles of the world (Insecta, Coleoptera &quot; Geadephaga &quot;: Trachypachidae and Carabidae incl. Paussinae, Cicinidelinae, Rhysodinae). Privately published, W. Lorenz, Tutzing, iv + 502 pp." year="1998 a">Lorenz (1998a)</bibRefCitation>
, but we question his generic placement. Recourse to the type in Paris will solve the problem.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
